--- !u!114 &5842581
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 5842574}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 31629047cadc70941a4f1725fe6382fe, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::CelestialBody
  bodyName: Neptune
  labelColor: {r: 0, g: 0.0627451, b: 1, a: 1}
  profileImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 38cd1686daf57e340bac8d6398cabefe, type: 3}
  profileDescription: <b>Neptune, the eighth and farthest planet from the Sun</b>,
    is known for its pale blue color, intense weather systems, and supersonic winds.
    As an ice giant similar to Uranus, Neptune is a cold, remote world with a unique
    atmosphere and dynamic storms.\n\nNamed after the Roman god of the sea, Neptune
    remains a mysterious and intriguing planet at the outer edge of our Solar System.
  stats:
  - label: Mass
    value: <b>1.02 x 10<sup>26</sup>kg</b>
  - label: Diameter
    value: <b>49,528 km</b>
  - label: Distance to Sun
    value: <b>4,515 million km</b>
  - label: Orbital Period
    value: <b>164 years</b>
  - label: Length of Day
    value: <b>16.1 hours</b>
  - label: Gravity
    value: <b>11 m/s<sup>2</sup></b>
  - label: Satellite count
    value: 16
  - label: Temperature (mean)
    value: "<b>-200 \xB0C</b>"
  - label: Atmosphere
    value: H2+He
  orbitCharacteristicsDescription: <b>Neptune orbits the Sun</b> at an average distance
    of approximately 4.5 billion kilometers (2.8 billion miles), making it the most
    distant of the eight planets. It takes Neptune around 165 Earth years to complete
    one orbit, so a single year on Neptune is longer than the entire modern history
    of humanity.\n\nNeptune's rotation period is about 16 hours, giving it a short
    day compared to its long year.\n\nAlthough distant, Neptune's mass exerts a significant
    gravitational influence on nearby objects, affecting the orbits of Kuiper Belt
    objects and dwarf planets like Pluto.
  structureDescription: <b>Neptune's structure is similar to Uranus's</b>, with a
    small rocky core composed of silicates and metals, surrounded by a mantle of
    water, ammonia, and methane ""ices."" This mantle is fluid under extreme pressures,
    contributing to Neptune's mass and density.\n\nThe outer layer is made up of
    molecular hydrogen and helium, with methane providing Neptune's signature pale
    blue color.\n\nNeptune's internal heat is greater than Uranus's, driving more
    dynamic atmospheric activity, including supersonic winds and transient storm
    systems such as the Great Dark Spot.
  atmosphereImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 33b1f90c0dc64bf4095f21498080a347, type: 3}
  atmosphereDescription: "<b>Neptune's atmosphere</b> is composed mainly of hydrogen
    and helium, with a small amount of methane that gives the planet its characteristic
    blue color. It has the most intense weather systems in the Solar System, with
    winds reaching up to 2,100 kilometers per hour (1,300 miles per hour).\\n\\nNeptune
    is known for its Great Dark Spot, a massive storm similar to Jupiter's Great
    Red Spot, though Neptune's storm systems appear and disappear over shorter timescales.
    The upper atmosphere is extremely cold, with temperatures dropping to -214\xB0C
    (-353\xB0F), yet Neptune radiates more energy than it receives from the Sun,
    suggesting an internal heat source."
  focusDistanceOverride: 0
  minFocusDistanceOverride: 0
  maxFocusDistanceOverride: 30
  galleryEntries: []
