  m_text: 'The Sun is the heart of our Solar System, a massive, glowing sphere of
    hot gas and plasma that provides the light and warmth essential for life on Earth.
    Classified as a G-type main-sequence star (often called a yellow dwarf), the
    Sun is one of billions of stars in our galaxy, but it holds a unique place in
    our sky and in sustaining the conditions for life as we know it.

