--- !u!114 &373012185
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 373012179}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 31629047cadc70941a4f1725fe6382fe, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::CelestialBody
  bodyName: Sun
  labelColor: {r: 1, g: 0.98823535, b: 0.36078432, a: 1}
  profileImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 13be78a5b5761794d9a064c0e78b884d, type: 3}
  profileDescription: <b>The Sun is the heart of our Solar System</b>, a massive,
    glowing sphere of hot gas and plasma that provides the light and warmth essential
    for life on Earth. Classified as a G-type main-sequence star (often called a
    yellow dwarf), the Sun is one of billions of stars in our galaxy, but it holds
    a unique place in our sky and in sustaining the conditions for life as we know
    it.
  stats:
  - label: Mass
    value: <b>1.99 x 10<sup>30</sup> kg</b>
  - label: Diameter
    value: <b>1,392,000 km</b>
  - label: Length of Day
    value: <b>9.9 hours</b>
  - label: Gravity
    value: <b>23.10 m/s<sup>2</sup></b>
  - label: Atmosphere
    value: <b>H2+He</b>
  - label: Temperature (Surface)
    value: "<b>5,000\xB0C</b>"
  orbitCharacteristicsDescription: 
  structureDescription: <b>The Sun's internal structure</b> consists of several layers
    essential to its energy production and Solar System influence. At the core, temperatures
    of 15 million degrees Celsius (27 million degrees Fahrenheit) enable nuclear
    fusion, converting hydrogen into helium and releasing immense energy. \n\nThe
    radiative zone surrounds the core, where energy moves outward through radiation
    over thousands of years.\n\nBeyond it lies the convective zone, where hot plasma
    rises and cooler plasma sinks, transporting energy to the surface.\n\nThe photosphere,
    the visible outer layer, emits the light and heat that reach Earth, while the
    chromosphere and corona extend millions of kilometers into space, reaching over
    a million degrees Celsius.
  atmosphereImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: ec57e13ba5da24d409280a178e27a408, type: 3}
  atmosphereDescription: "<b>The Sun's atmosphere</b> is composed of three main layers:
    the photosphere, chromosphere, and corona.\\n\\nThe photosphere, the Sun's visible
    surface, emits the light we see and has a temperature of about 5,500\xB0C (9,932\xB0F).
    Above it lies the chromosphere, a reddish layer visible during solar eclipses,
    where temperatures rise to around 20,000\xB0C (36,000\xB0F). The outermost layer,
    the corona, extends millions of kilometers into space and is incredibly hot,
    reaching temperatures of over 1 million degrees Celsius.\\n\\nThe Sun's atmosphere
    is dynamic, constantly releasing solar wind, a stream of charged particles that
    influences the entire Solar Svstem."
  focusDistanceOverride: 0
  minFocusDistanceOverride: 0
  maxFocusDistanceOverride: 30
  galleryEntries:
  - image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 61cbb6c11adc36d4487660b62f21db6b, type: 3}
    title: Sun Emits a Solstice CME
    description: This image from June 20 2013
