--- !u!114 &2120840424
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 2120840417}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 31629047cadc70941a4f1725fe6382fe, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::CelestialBody
  bodyName: Venus
  labelColor: {r: 1, g: 0.3372549, b: 0, a: 1}
  profileImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: ee6decdccb204f94abd8384a368460d5, type: 3}
  profileDescription: <b>Venus is the second planet from the Sun</b> and often called
    <b>Earth's sister planet</b> due to its similar size and composition. However,
    despite these surface similarities, Venus is an incredibly hostile world with
    crushing atmospheric pressure, scorching temperatures, and clouds of sulfuric
    acid.\n\nThis enigmatic planet has intrigued humans for centuries and remains
    a key focus of space exploration.
  stats:
  - label: Mass
    value: <b>4.87 x 10<sup>24</sup> kg</b>
  - label: Diameter
    value: <b>12,104 km</b>
  - label: Distance to Sun
    value: <b>108 million km</b>
  - label: Orbital Period
    value: <b>224.7 days</b>
  - label: Length of Day
    value: <b>117 days</b>
  - label: Gravity
    value: <b>8.90 m/s<sup>2</sup></b>
  - label: Satellite count
    value: 0
  - label: Temperature (mean)
    value: "<b>464 \xB0C</b>"
  - label: Atmosphere
    value: <b>CO2</b>
  orbitCharacteristicsDescription: '<b>Venus orbits the Sun</b> at an average distance
    of about 108 million kilometers (67 million miles), making it the second closest
    planet to our star. Its orbit is almost perfectly circular, and it takes 225
    Earth days to complete a full orbit around the Sun.\n\nInterestingly, Venus has
    a unique rotation: it rotates in the opposite direction of most planets, meaning
    the Sun would appear to rise in the west and set in the east.\n\nAdditionally,
    Venus has an incredibly slow rotation period, taking 243 Earth days to complete
    one full spin on its axis, making its day longer than its year.'
  structureDescription: <b>Venus's internal structure</b> consists of a central iron-nickel
    core, roughly 3,000 kilometers (1,865 miles) in radius, similar in proportion
    to Earth's core.\n\nSurrounding the core is a silicate mantle that drives the
    planet's extensive volcanic activity. However, unlike Earth, Venus lacks plate
    tectonics, which means heat from the mantle builds up and escapes through widespread
    volcanic resurfacing events.\n\nThe outer crust of Venus, composed primarily
    of basaltic rock, is relatively thin-about 10-20 kilometers (6-12 miles) and
    is marked by vast lava plains and towering volcanic mountains, such as Maxwell
    Montes.
  atmosphereImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 28736df7720385d4794795d54d473553, type: 3}
  atmosphereDescription: "<b>Venus has a thick and toxic atmosphere</b> composed
    mainly of carbon dioxide, with clouds of sulfuric acid that shroud its surface
    from view. This dense atmosphere creates a powerful greenhouse effect, trapping
    heat and raising surface temperatures to around 465\xB0C (869\xB0F)-hot enough
    to melt lead.\\n\\nThe atmospheric pressure on Venus's surface is 92 times greater
    than Earth's, equivalent to being nearly a kilometer underwater on Earth. High-speed
    winds in the upper atmosphere circle the planet in just a few days, creating
    a dynamic weather system above the harsh surface."
  focusDistanceOverride: 0
  minFocusDistanceOverride: 0.35
  maxFocusDistanceOverride: 30
  galleryEntries: []
